<br>
&quot;What is assist?&quot;<br>
<br>
Then once you explain it to them, I hear...<br>
<br>
&quot;It doesn't work! So I am not bothering.&quot;<br>
<br>
*sigh*<br>
<br>
I spent 5 hours do the orc group in Highpass, basically running the show (picked up level 18 thankfully). I can't believe how many times I had to explain &quot;assist&quot; and the idea &quot;attacking the largest (and casters) first&quot; to the group. I managed not to die at all, but our cleric had to run for zone a few times. I got tells from the cleric and the lead tank in group wondering if they would ever learn, I couldn't help but laugh. He joked, &quot;I might as well cast AOE spells and save the tanks the trouble of breaking all your mezzing.&quot;<br>
<br>
Why do I have the feeling this woe of mine (and every chanter) won't be going away for a long time?? I know everyone goes through a growing process and I am on green sever (newbies galore!!), but boy does it get frustrating over time. <br>
<br>
Oh well, I still love being one of the few, the proud, the mezzing, the Chanters!!<br>
<br>
*smiles* <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccb9b><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/ucolodagh.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Colodagh</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/misc_1.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#330000>(1/3/01 12:15:37 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub136.ezboard.com/feqenchantersrealmstories.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.geocities.com/burncrash76/CELTIC10.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Mentally Handicapped</span><hr size=1> disband stupid newbie #1<br>
